$ VBA: function and sub parameters
@ parameter

→ development/languages/VBA/language/subs-and-functions/optional-parameters[Optional parameters]

The optional declaration of a parameter with → development/languages/VBA/language/subs-and-functions/byVal-byRef[`byVal` or `byRef`] allows to pass a parameter *by reference* or as *copied value*.

When calling a function or sub, there are cases when → development/languages/VBA/language/subs-and-functions/call-with-without-parantheses[parantheses are required or can be omited].

The → development/languages/VBA/language/subs-and-functions/parameters/paramArray[`paramArray`] keyword allows to
pass an arbitrary number of arguments to a sub or function.


